content: Brilliant!
Best app out there. Worth it.
The best of its kind. Loving it. Using it every day in my practice.
Bought the phone app to support the awesome web site, but the app is fantastic as well.

This app should be a tool for any musician. I'm studying chord theory and am a new music writer. This app is worth every penny. The only two additions I hope for in the future for this app is a more direct way of seeing the inversions of each type of chord and a feature where you're able to punch in a chord progression...for the writer side of things . Besides that this app seriously delivers invaluable immediate information on chords, its all there. There's a site you can try this out for free.

I am extremely happy to have found out that there's an app version of this website I've been using for free for months now. Bought it right away and have been blown away by the quality of the app as well! Thank you Oliver, please keep updating the app and the website ðŸ¤˜
Perfect app to find names of weird chords ðŸ‘ŒðŸ‘ŒðŸ‘Œ

I couldn't be happier with the app. I can never really write songs using just music theory and whatnot so I end up using my ear and not knowing what key i'm in or what mode i'm using or what the chords are a lot of the time, because they're chord variations or weird extensions. This app allows me to know exactly what chords i'm playing and allows me to move the root around to give me options when creating progressions. The only problem is they don't have a scales app as well.
Best guitar chord app I've ever used!
Love the website but the app is non-functional on my chromebook.
I'd give 1000 stars if I could. Really amazing app, absolutely worth the money!
Best chord library and analyzer in the playstore!
This app is great, I've been using the website version for years and it's really helped me! The app also comes with music theory quizzes which are great for testing your knowledge!
I've used the browser version for a while and just had to get the app to support the developer, it's so incredibly useful. No single app has been better for developing my music theory knowledge.
Really great but unfortunately there's no left handed version(?)
replyContent: Hi Andrew, sorry for the long wait, but here it is! A freshly released update featuring the long-awaited left-hand mode! Oliver

content: The Oolimo website has been super useful to me for quite a while. I didn't know about the app till now. I purchased it right away. I have no doubt this will be great, that's why I already gave it 5 stars. Cheers! (request : Full scales? And prevent screen sleep?) Thanks a ton.
Love this app for analyzing complex chords
Always wondered what the name of those crazy chords I played were. Now I know. Very good app
having downloaded it it would not Allow notes on the vitual fretboard!!
replyContent: Hi John,  Iâ€˜m sorry that you are experiencing such a problem. Did you upgrade the app or was it a new installation? If you contact me at oliver@oolimo.com, we can communicate and hopefully find what causes your troubles. Kind regards, Oliver

content: Love this app. One of the few I've paid for and well worth many times what it cost. I use it every day. I had some issues and the response from the creator was immediate. (The issue was with my phone - not the app) I originally wrote a negative review after it stopped working because I was heartbroken I could no longer use it! All is well, now.
replyContent: Hi Wayne, Iâ€˜m glad everything works fine now :-) Thanks for taking the time to report that success and for giving 5 stars again! I also learned something new here. I will try to find a way to prevent that files are loaded from the phones cache storage after an update in the future. Kind regards, Oliver

content: Fresh layout and features not found in similar apps. Contains quizzes and exercises that help the beginner and intermediate guitarist. App also explains theory of chords and how they are most likely used. Great App!
Lots to like and good potential, but some poor decisions with the UI (clicking on the menu loses you your current screen), and omissions (inversions on the chord finder screen).
replyContent: Hi Pedr, the last chord and most important settings are kept stored now (since version 1.1.4). To see the inversion of a chord finders chord, just tap on the analyzer icon and your actual chord will be shown in the analyzer with all inversions. Kind regards, Oliver

content: I have used the Oolimo website for years and found it very helpful for song writing chord tracking and for understanding music theory. This appears to be a reasonably faithful rendition of the same thing with the added benefits of being offline and in my pocket.

A potentially good app spoiled by a poor user interface. What's worse, there are quiz questions that are incomprehensible because little effort was put into what seems to be a translation. This is not rocket science.
replyContent: Hi Colin, I'm sorry that you don't like the user interface. So far it seemed to me that most users really like it. Feel free to report any bugs, mistakes, incomprehensibilities or suggestions to oliver@oolimo.com. Nobody is perfect, but everthing can improve with the help of the community. Oliver

content: Money well spent. Fantastic app if you're a guitarist. I would like a scales version of this app.
A brilliant app. Easy to use and an invaluable tool for any guitarist.
Great app, great and easy user interface with a multitude of functions. A must have for every serious guitarist

Amazing app, have nothing negative to say. Have you ever thought of adding a feature where you can create and save chord progressions, I'm aware of the ability to save chords I'm more so thinking progressions as a whole. I often use Oolimo to create different chords/inversions and I would love to be able to create unique progressions on the go.
replyContent: Thanks for giving Oolimo a great rating although you're missing a feature you'd like to have. There are many things I want to add in the future. I'm currently working to implement  the quiz with the next update in august. Then some interactive theory and for sure also Chord progressions! I'm giving my best but have to ask for patience! Oliver

content: I wrote some music a awhile back and I didn't know the name for the chords and now I found my answers. I feel happy about this. Thank you!
Invaluable app for guitarists. Very straightforward and the interface is really clean.
Incredible app for chord finding and analysis. It even contains written out descriptions of the chords with recommendations on common use! Has Light and Dark mode and a fantastic UI.
Great for anybody playing the guitar!
